One of South Africa's longest-running festivals Splashy Fen attracts hordes of music fans to a farm in the region annually.The South African Weather Service in Durban warned that a cold front sweeping over KwaZulu-Natal has brought with it a dramatic drop in temperature for the weekend.Light snow is only expected to fall in Lesotho but rain and cooler temperatures are predicted for the province."Minimum temperatures will be between two and five degrees and maximum temperatures will reach between 17 and 20 degrees in the Underberg region " said meteorologist Aslam Fardiwalla.He said conditions are expected to improve by Sunday.- TMG Digital/TimesLIVE